th two auxilliary parameters. As a\nresult, we obtain a family of \"maximally hyperfractal\" compact sets and\nrelative fractal drums (i.e., such that the associated fractal zeta functions\nhave a singularity at every point of the critical line of convergence).\nFinally, we discuss the general fractal tube formulas and the Minkowski\nmeasurability criterion obtained by the authors in the context of relative\nfractal drums (and, in particular, of bounded subsets of the N-dimensional\nEuclidean space).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Feb 2015 14:49:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Feb 2015 20:42:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 31 May 2015 19:06:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
